text:
Hi Stephan, 
Thank you!
The list of environments you see in jupyter notebook is actually the kernel and not your virtual environment. You can use the default "Python 3 (ipykernel)" from any virtual environment to run your code. 

But in case you want to create a kernel by the name of your virtual environment then you can do that as well using the below command. You can run it in terminal from the desired virtual environment.
ipython kernel install --user --name=YT-env
